        "description": "This project guides you on how to create crayon drip art. By melting crayons onto paper or card, you can produce unique and colorful designs for decoration or gifts.",
        "steps": [
            "Gather your materials: crayons, paper or card, a hair dryer, and blu tack or tape.",
            "Choose your desired crayon colors.",
            "Attach one crayon to the top of your paper or card using blu tack or tape.",
            "Hold the paper/card vertically and use the hair dryer to melt the crayon. The melting crayon will drip down the card.",
            "Tilt the card at an angle to control the direction of the crayon drips.",
            "Repeat the melting and dripping process with different colors until you achieve your desired effect.",
            "Once the crayon art is dry, you can either paint over it with black paint for a contrasting effect or leave the white background."
